title: Palo Alto: Panorama Availability
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/network/palo_alto
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors whether a Palo Alto firewall is connected to its
 configured Panorama management servers. It reads the connection state
 from the PAN-COMMON-MIB (panMgmtPanoramaConnected .1.3.6.1.4.1.25461.2.1.2.4.1
 and panMgmtPanorama2Connected .1.3.6.1.4.1.25461.2.1.2.4.2).

 The service is {OK} when the reported state is "Connected" and {CRIT}
 otherwise.

item:
 The Panorama slot number, "1" for the primary and "2" for the secondary
 Panorama server.

discovery:
 One service is created for each Panorama slot that reports a state.
